EmailTemplate.subject: DR Building Dreams - Final Email
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Hey everyone!
I have already sent this information out before in another email, but I just wanted to send it out again just incase anyone has forgotten.
PASSPORTS It is very important that everyone brings two photocopies of their passport while travelling. We will be collecting one when you arrive, and the other one is for you to store in a separate location than your physical passport.
EMERGENCY MEDICAL INSURANCE Everyone is required to purchase their own travel emergency medical insurance for the dates that they are travelling outside of your country. Please forward this information to me as soon as possible. Travel Insurance Provider: Policy #: Policy Name (if applicable): Policy Phone #1: Policy Phone #2:
CHECKED BAGGAGE Please check with your airlines to see what checked baggage requirements need to be met. Most airlines require checked baggage to be no more than 50 lbs and the first baggage is either free or there is a $25 fee. Any extra baggage will result in an additional cost.
EXCURSIONS - OPTIONAL There are some excursions being offered on your day off - and they are a blast! Activities will be explained and announced on your first night in Dominican Republic, after the Dominican Trip Hosts speaks with your trip leader (Kelci), the costs of full day excursion are generally between $80-90 USD.
EMERGENCY CONTACTS If your family needs to contact you in case of emergency while in Dominican Republic, these are the numbers to call. Live Different Office (Canada) - 1-866-432-4464
Emergency 24 hour number (Dominican Repubilic): Kelly (Emergency Contact) - 809 991 2043 Kent - 809 991 2661
Sosua by the Sea front desk - 1-809-571-3222. Please either leave a message or ask for the Live Different office/Kelly Fearon (111) or your son or daughter's room number if you know it.
For general inquiries and non-urgent matters, please contact us via email joy@livedifferent. Emails are checked regularly throughout the day and someone will be scheduled in the office from 8am - 5pm EST. Someone will be available to answer the emergency phone number 24 hours/day.
PHONE AND INTERNET ACCESS Calling cards do not often work in the DR as 1-800 are not collect and will cost you money to call. Some past participants have put international plans on their cell phones prior to leaving but you will need to contact your cell service provider to see if this is possible. There is a internet cafe and wifi available for purchase at the resort and you can use skype to call family as well. The internet minute prices for wireless and the cafe are approximately $2 for an hour, $5 for a day, $25 for the week (USD). Some people like to bring their laptops as well, but keep in mind that Live Different is not responsible for lost or stolen items. There are safes available in the rooms for smaller valuable items, but they are not large enough to fit most laptops.
A DAY IN THE LIFE OF... This summer you will have a chance to participate in one of the most impacting experiences that our Live Different Build trips have to offer called, "A Day in the Life of...". This is our day to invite volunteers into the homes of families in the community we work in (1/2 day max). On this day, volunteers will have an opportunity to cook and clean alongside a family and learn the every day challenges of a typical family in Dominican Republic.
SPENDING MONEY/CURRENCY It is best to bring USD cash with you, CDN cash will also be accepted but USD will be easier. If you choose to purchase an excursion on your day off, the only other things you will need to pay for with your spending money is:
*Your meals while traveling to and from your departure city to and from Dominican Republic. *Any personal spending, souvenirs, or snacks purchased at the store. *$30 USD Resort staff tip. *$20 USD for a night out for dinner in a fun beach town with your team (this is optional, please speak to your trip leader if you will be doing this on your trip.
FAMILY PROFILES Projects and families have been decided and photos and bios are up on the website and the information was sent out in the beginning of summer.
PROJECT PAGE We have set up a project page which will be updated daily: http://livedifferent.com/private-trips/building-dreams-aug-2013/details
On this trip page, under the "PROJECT" tab, will be where your family and friends can see daily updates, links to the photos on our Live Different facebook page, and the trip blogs, (look out, I may be asking you to help me write a blog...volunteers needed!!) Once your trip has started, feel free to tell your friends and family to check this page out daily, (hint, if you email this link to them or post it on your facebook, it's a lot easier for them to find it!). We do our best to post a blog everyday but sometimes there are issues with the resort's internet.
PACKING LIST A packing list is attached for all who need it again. One great thing to pack that is not on the list is Gatorade mix for your water, which helps to replenish your electrolytes after working hard in the hot sun! Sanitizer wipes are also pretty handy to have before you eat your packed lunches too. Don't forget BUG SPRAY!!!
Talk to you guys soon!
